	      <div class="thumbnail">
	        <p><strong>Pandemic Eats!!</strong></p>
	        <p><i>Michelle Smith</i></p>
	        <p>Sometimes I get so ashamed that I can't cook, despite being 30 years old. I still rely on my mom's cooking skills to get me through the day... Well, she finally got tired of baby-ing me, and told me I had to cook - then she stopped sending over her food to my apartment! So, living alone, being 30, nothing to do in this situation - I took her advice and started cooking. Against all odds, I've finally learnt how to cook!</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="col-sm-4">
	      <div class="thumbnail">
	        <p><strong>I Regret Hating School!</strong></p>
	        <p><i>Bob Keele</i></p>
	        <p>Often I used to complain to everyone around me how I HATED going to school so early (8:45 AM) to school. Now, I'm bored out of my mind ever since things closed down. I had nothing to do but work part-time, which wasn't much honestly. I realized how much I missed my school, meeting my friends, annoying teachers, all of it. My sleep schedule is all messed and I'm bored, I want to go to school!</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="col-sm-4">
	      <div class="thumbnail">
	        <p><strong>Nothing Changed</strong></p>
	        <p><i>Chantelle Ross</i></p>
	        <p>Everyone has these cool stories about how they're learning new things, doing innovative stuff at home. I'm just here doing my regular activities. Some people are hysterical and talking about how much they miss their friend's pet cat, or going for bubble tea with their friends every two seconds. Nothing has changed for me though. Pandemic? Lockdown? Social distancing? I don't care. I was an introvert anyway</p>
